        <p>So, thanks for reading, that's everything.</p>
        
        <p>If we want to see if carbon offsets actually work — if you want to even seem them do what they were <em>designed for</em> — we need to count removed carbon, in real-time, on a continuously updated basis.</p>
        
        <h4>If we're going to count, we must count.</h4>

